reviews.text: Our first time at this restaurant.  The whole seabass was nice, but both the lamb shank and chicken wrapped in bacon were overdone. Mushroom risotto was nice. However, the service was poor. We ordered starters and main courses. All the main courses arrived before starters. We ordered a bottle of red wine which arrived really warm. This was subsequently changed after we brought it to the attention of the staff.  All in all not an impressive experience.

Great western cuisine! Romantic and wonderful environment with good service, lots of customers to have dinner or happy hour for chatting. We ordered lots of dishes and highly recommended the lamb with rosemary sauce, prawn with spicy sauce and brownies with ice-cream. We all enjoyed a lot in this dining
A comfortable place to relax and enjoy the meal in the sunny afternoon. The staff are great, very attentive and friendly. Highly recommended!

There is a 50% off deal on Eatigo. It’s my third time to the restaurant. Love the grilled sea bass. Tried their lamb shank for the first time, and it was pretty good also. Good place to chill for brunch/lunches.
Ordered the huge steak on their specials menu. Overcooked, cheap quality meat, and lots of fat. Service was great.
